[size=18][b]TRACK NOTES[/b][/size]
  [i]What... you really thought I'd write up a turn-by-turn guide for the whole Nordschleife?![/i] :D

Fortunately there are many great lap guides available online - reply below with your favorites!

Regardless, some important notes:
       - There are not many overtaking opportunities early on in the lap - especially on lap 1, BE PATIENT and you will have plenty of chances later on.
       - The SRF really doesn't like the kerbs, especially on the exits of corners - be careful!
       - The relatively low power of the SRF makes many of the faster corners easy flat-out with a small lift.

Daniil has posted a very safe and easy-to-drive setup [url=http://members.iracing.com/jforum/posts/list/200/3349192.page#9443179]HERE[/url] (also attached to this post). It understeers quite a lot, but it is easy to drive fast and is friendlier over the kerbs than the baseline.


